<subSubSection id="FEB4EF82FF85FFDFFF57FC74AFA7F99C" pageId="11" pageNumber="327" type="description">
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF85FFDFFF57FC74AFF2FC14" blockId="11.[151,1437,909,1801]" box="[151,493,909,934]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">
Female. Body length: 
<quantity id="715611ECFF85FFDFFE50FC77AFF6FC14" box="[400,489,910,934]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="327" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF85FFDFFF07FC48AEF6FBEB" blockId="11.[151,1437,909,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF85FFDFFF07FC48AF00FC78" box="[199,287,945,969]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">Colour:</emphasis>
head entirely yellow or light brown, palpi yellow, flagellum dark brown with seven white flagellomeres at the apex, scape brown; mesosoma dark brown to black with lighter propodeum; first tergum light brown, terga II–V black with lighter striae at base of terga II, terga VI with black base and yellow apex, tergum VII entirely yellow; wing veins dark brown and lighter stigma; legs yellow with coxae and base of the femur pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF85FFDFFF07FB9CAB11FB13" blockId="11.[151,1437,909,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF85FFDFFF07FB9CAF1BFBCC" box="[199,260,1125,1149]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">Head</emphasis>
: vertex, frons and face smooth; malar space greater than ¼ eye height; temple narrow, width shorter than ½ eye width; ocell-ocular distance 2.5 times greater than diameter of lateral ocellus; 22 flagellomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF85FFDFFF07FB57AF2CFA2F" blockId="11.[151,1437,909,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">
Mesosoma: 
<taxonomicName id="71AEC78AFF85FFDFFE92FB54AFFCFB77" box="[338,483,1197,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Heterospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopleuron">mesopleuron</taxonomicName>
smooth, precoxal sulcus smooth, shorter than width of 
<taxonomicName id="71AEC78AFF85FFDFFBADFB54AB1DFB77" box="[1133,1282,1197,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Heterospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopleuron">mesopleuron</taxonomicName>
; mesoscutum lobes smooth and hairy just along notauli; notauli scrobiculate meeting before prescutellar furrow in triangular rugose area; prescutellar furrow with one cross carina; scutellum smooth; propodeum with basal median areas distinct and margined, basal median areas smooth, basal median carina present, areolar margin distinct, areolar area smooth-rugose, lateral areas smooth, mesosternum smooth. 
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF85FFDFFC80FAC7ADABFAE4" box="[832,948,1342,1365]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">Fore wing</emphasis>
: vein r shorter than vein 3 
<collectingCountry id="CEB9FC99FF85FFDFFB24FAC7AB08FAE7" box="[1252,1303,1342,1366]" name="South Africa" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">RSa</collectingCountry>
, vein 1cu-a beyond vein 1M, stigma wider than length of vein r. 
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF85FFDFFD29FA98AD76FAC8" box="[745,873,1377,1401]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">Hind wing:</emphasis>
vein SC+R present, length of vein M+CU shorter than vein 
<specimenCount id="A0A87780FF85FFDFFEC5FA7FAF2CFA2F" box="[261,307,1414,1438]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327" type="generic">1M.</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF85FFDFFF07FA53AFA7F99C" blockId="11.[151,1437,909,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF85FFDFFF07FA53AF5AFA70" box="[199,325,1450,1473]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">Metasoma:</emphasis>
first tergum granulose-rugose, apical width shorter than length; second tergum costate-granulose, apical width three times greater than length; third tergum smooth; terga II+III with anterior transverse groove present and nearly sinuose; posterior transverse groove present; terga IV–VII smooth; ovipositor equal to length of first tergum of metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
